{"id":"351062650_A_C1_composite_spline_Hermite_interpolant_on_the_sphere","abstract":"In this paper, we identified the sphere‐like surface by a rectangular domain. We constructed a new interpolant on the sphere using the tensor product of the quadratic composite‐spline interpolant and the third‐order trigonometric composite‐spline interpolant. This construction on the rectangular domain is described in detail, with the study and the proof of the error bounds of each interpolant. Furthermore, we present numerical examples to show the efficiency of this method.","authors":["Salah Bouhiri","Abdellah Lamnii","Mohamed Lamnii","A. Zidna"],"meta":["September 2021Mathematical Methods in the Applied Sciences 44(1)","DOI:10.1002/mma.7497"],"references":["337467567_On_algebraic_trigonometric_integro_splines","242980779_Unified_and_extended_form_of_three_types_of_splines","228694900_Spherical_spline_solution_to_a_PDE_on_the_sphere","225729317_The_BS_class_of_Hermite_spline_quasi-interpolants_on_nonuniform_knot_distributions","308960473_Computation_of_Hermite_interpolation_in_terms_of_B-spline_basis_using_polar_forms","242979012_An_algorithm_for_fitting_data_over_a_circle_using_tensor_product_splines","227248461_A_Family_of_Spline_Quasi-Interpolants_on_the_Sphere","226930548_Fitting_scattered_data_on_spherelike_surfaces_using_tensor_products_of_trigonometric_and_polynomial_splines","226808855_A_General_Multiresolution_Method_for_Fitting_Functions_on_the_Sphere","226360469_A_multiresolution_method_for_fitting_scattered_data_on_the_sphere","223833228_Fitting_scattered_data_on_sphere-like_surfaces_using_spherical_splines","223068885_Construction_of_spherical_spline_quasi-interpolants_based_on_blossoming","222468821_GB-splines_of_arbitrary_order","222453699_Bernstein-Bezier_polynomials_on_spheres_and_sphere-like_surfaces","222338721_Cubic_spline_quasi-interpolants_on_Powell-Sabin_partitions"]}